NG Nordic Finland Oy
NG Nordic is a leading Nordic provider of circular solutions and environmental services. Through reuse, collection, recycling, and depollution, NG Nordic transforms waste into valuable resources and removes hazardous substances from circulation – scaling access to circular raw materials, decarbonizing society, and helping protect natural ecosystems.

In the field of plastics, NG Nordic offers a growing portfolio of innovative and sustainable materials and services across the entire value chain, from collection to recycling and reuse. This includes product brands such as Circo® recycled plastics, a low-carbon alternative to virgin plastic, and INGA – plastics born from CO₂, a future-oriented raw material solution. Furthermore, Letbek, a subsidiary of NG Nordic, specializes in circular plastic solutions, using recycled plastic as a resource to create new, durable products.

With a strong presence across the Nordics, as well as in Poland and the UK, NG Nordic is a vital part of the region’s industrial infrastructure, handling 4.4 million tonnes of waste annually through 90 facilities and sites. With 3,400 employees, the company generates EUR 1.3 billion in revenue and provides tailored customer solutions across the entire value chain.

